  <!-- IRP -->
  <section class="irp">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header">
        <span class="section-tag">International Registration Plan</span>
        <h2>IRP: International Registration Plan</h2>
      </div>

      <div class="content-grid">
        <div class="content-main">
          <h3>What It Is</h3>
          <p>IRP is the registration system for commercial vehicles traveling across state lines. Instead of buying plates in every state you haul through, IRP lets you register once and pay fees proportionally based on the miles you drive in each jurisdiction.</p>

          <h3>Who Needs It</h3>
          <p>You need IRP registration if your vehicle:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Has two axles and a gross vehicle weight (GVW) over <strong>26,000 lbs</strong>, OR</li>
            <li>Has three or more axles regardless of weight, OR</li>
            <li>Is used in combination when the combined weight exceeds 26,000 lbs</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="note"><strong>Exception:</strong> Vehicles operating only within Idaho don't need IRP. But the moment you cross a state line for commercial purposes, you need it.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="content-sidebar">
          <div class="process-box">
            <h4>How to Get IRP in Idaho</h4>
            <ol>
              <li><strong>Gather your documents:</strong>
                <ul>
                  <li>Proof of vehicle ownership (title or lease agreement)</li>
                  <li>USDOT number</li>
                  <li>Vehicle identification info (VIN, year, make)</li>
                  <li>Estimated miles per jurisdiction</li>
                </ul>
              </li>
              <li><strong>File through Idaho's Commercial Registration System:</strong>
                <ul>
                  <li>Portal: <a href="https://crs.idaho.celtic-host.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">crs.idaho.celtic-host.com</a></li>
                  <li>Or contact CVS directly: cvs@itd.idaho.gov | 208-872-3163</li>
                </ul>
              </li>
              <li><strong>Pay your fees:</strong> Based on the miles you project traveling in each state.</li>
              <li><strong>Receive your cab card:</strong> This goes in your truck. It lists every jurisdiction where you're registered to operate.</li>
            </ol>
            <p class="renewal-note"><strong>Renewal:</strong> IRP runs on an annual cycle. Renew before expiration to avoid operating on expired credentials.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- IFTA -->
  <section class="ifta">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header">
        <span class="section-tag">Fuel Tax</span>
        <h2>IFTA: International Fuel Tax Agreement</h2>
      </div>

      <div class="content-grid">
        <div class="content-main">
          <h3>What It Is</h3>
          <p>IFTA simplifies fuel tax reporting for carriers operating in multiple states. Instead of filing separate fuel tax returns in every state, you file one quarterly report with Idaho and they distribute taxes owed to other jurisdictions.</p>

          <h3>Who Needs It</h3>
          <p>You need IFTA if you operate a qualified motor vehicle (over 26,000 lbs or 3+ axles) in two or more IFTA jurisdictions. If you only run in Idaho, you don't need IFTA - but most commercial truckers cross state lines.</p>

          <h3>What You Report</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Total miles driven in each jurisdiction</li>
            <li>Total gallons of fuel purchased in each jurisdiction</li>
            <li>Fuel tax owed (or credit if you bought fuel in high-tax states)</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="content-sidebar">
          <div class="schedule-box">
            <h4>Quarterly Filing Schedule</h4>
            <table>
              <thead>
                <tr><th>Quarter</th><th>Period</th><th>Due Date</th></tr>
              </thead>
              <tbody>
                <tr><td>Q1</td><td>Jan-Mar</td><td>April 30</td></tr>
                <tr><td>Q2</td><td>Apr-Jun</td><td>July 31</td></tr>
                <tr><td>Q3</td><td>Jul-Sep</td><td>October 31</td></tr>
                <tr><td>Q4</td><td>Oct-Dec</td><td>January 31</td></tr>
              </tbody>
            </table>
          </div>

          <div class="file-box">
            <h4>Where to File</h4>
            <ul>
              <li>Portal: <a href="https://crs.idaho.celtic-host.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">crs.idaho.celtic-host.com</a></li>
              <li>Email: cvs@itd.idaho.gov</li>
              <li>Phone: 208-872-3163</li>
            </ul>
            <p class="warning"><strong>Penalty for late filing:</strong> Interest accrues on unpaid taxes, plus potential license revocation if you don't file for multiple quarters.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- UCR -->
  <section class="ucr">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header">
        <span class="section-tag">Federal Registration</span>
        <h2>UCR: Unified Carrier Registration</h2>
      </div>

      <div class="content-block">
        <h3>What It Is</h3>
        <p>UCR is an annual federal registration requirement for interstate carriers. The fees fund state motor carrier safety programs and enforcement.</p>

        <h3>Who Needs It</h3>
        <p>If you operate commercial motor vehicles in interstate commerce - hauling across state lines - you need UCR. This includes:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Motor carriers</li>
          <li>Freight brokers</li>
          <li>Leasing companies</li>
          <li>Freight forwarders</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="fee-table">
        <h3>UCR Fees by Fleet Size</h3>
        <table>
          <thead>
            <tr><th>Fleet Size</th><th>2024 Fee</th></tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr><td>0-2 vehicles</td><td><strong>$176</strong></td></tr>
            <tr><td>3-5 vehicles</td><td><strong>$362</strong></td></tr>
            <tr><td>6-20 vehicles</td><td><strong>$730</strong></td></tr>
            <tr><td>21-100 vehicles</td><td><strong>$1,813</strong></td></tr>
            <tr><td>101-1,000 vehicles</td><td><strong>$8,539</strong></td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
        <p>Register at <a href="https://www.ucr.gov" target="_blank" rel="noopener">ucr.gov</a> or through Idaho CVS.</p>
        <p class="deadline"><strong>Deadline:</strong> UCR runs on a calendar year (Jan 1 - Dec 31). Register before operating in the new year.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- HVUT -->
  <section class="hvut">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header">
        <span class="section-tag">IRS Form 2290</span>
        <h2>HVUT: Heavy Vehicle Use Tax</h2>
      </div>

      <div class="content-grid">
        <div class="content-main">
          <h3>What It Is</h3>
          <p>HVUT is a federal tax on heavy vehicles using public highways. The IRS collects this tax - not Idaho - and the revenue funds highway maintenance.</p>

          <h3>Who Needs It</h3>
          <p>You owe HVUT if your vehicle has a taxable gross weight of <strong>55,000 lbs or more</strong>.</p>

          <h3>The Tax</h3>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Annual tax:</strong> $100-$550 depending on weight</li>
            <li><strong>Tax year:</strong> July 1 through June 30</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="content-sidebar">
          <div class="hvut-box">
            <h4>When to File</h4>
            <p><strong>Filing period:</strong> July 1 through September 30</p>
            <p>If you put a new vehicle on the road mid-year, file by the last day of the month following the month you first used it.</p>

            <h4>Where to File</h4>
            <p><strong>File directly with the IRS</strong> - not with Idaho:</p>
            <ul>
              <li>E-file through IRS-approved providers</li>
              <li>Paper Form 2290 to IRS</li>
              <li>You'll receive a stamped Schedule 1 proving payment</li>
            </ul>

            <div class="critical-note">
              <strong>Why this matters:</strong> You can't register a vehicle over 55,000 lbs without a stamped Schedule 1. IRP won't process your registration without proof of HVUT payment.
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- COMPLIANCE CHECKLIST -->
  <section class="checklist">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header centered">
        <span class="section-tag">Summary</span>
        <h2>Staying Compliant: The Checklist</h2>
      </div>

