            <td>Quarterly</td>
            <td>Idaho CVS</td>
            <td>End of month after quarter</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>UCR Registration</td>
            <td>Annual</td>
            <td>UCR.gov or Idaho CVS</td>
            <td>January 1</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>HVUT (Form 2290)</td>
            <td>Annual</td>
            <td>IRS</td>
            <td>September 30</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- HOW RMS HELPS -->
  <section class="rms-helps">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header">
        <span class="section-tag">RMS Advantage</span>
        <h2>How RMS Truck Insurance Helps With Compliance</h2>
      </div>

      <div class="help-content">
        <p class="intro">Insurance and compliance go together. You can't bind a policy on a truck that's not legally registered, and you can't haul legal freight without proper coverage.</p>

        <h3>What RMS Does Before Binding</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Verify IRP is current</strong> - We check your cab card expiration before writing a policy</li>
          <li><strong>Confirm IFTA status</strong> - Lapsed IFTA means you're not legally operating interstate</li>
          <li><strong>Check UCR registration</strong> - Required for all interstate carriers</li>
          <li><strong>Validate HVUT payment</strong> - Stamped Schedule 1 proves you're compliant</li>
        </ul>

        <div class="why-matters">
          <strong>Why this matters to you:</strong> Some agents will bind your insurance without checking compliance. Then you get pulled over in Oregon, DOT finds your IRP lapsed, and you're parked. Your insurance was valid, but you weren't legal to operate. RMS catches these issues before they cost you a load.
        </div>

        <p>We know Idaho's requirements because we work with Idaho truckers daily. New authority or established carrier - we verify your filings are current before we bind your coverage.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- IDAHO CVS CONTACT -->
  <section class="contact">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header centered">
        <span class="section-tag">Contact</span>
        <h2>Idaho CVS Contact Information</h2>
      </div>

      <div class="contact-card">
        <h3>Commercial Vehicle Services</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Email:</strong> cvs@itd.idaho.gov</li>
          <li><strong>Phone:</strong> 208-872-3163</li>
          <li><strong>Online Portal:</strong> <a href="https://crs.idaho.celtic-host.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">crs.idaho.celtic-host.com</a></li>
        </ul>
        <p>For IRP, IFTA, and UCR questions, CVS is your direct contact at Idaho Transportation Department.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- RELATED GUIDES -->
  <section class="related">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header">
        <span class="section-tag">More Idaho Guides</span>
        <h2>Related Idaho Trucking Guides</h2>
      </div>

      <div class="related-grid">
        <a href="/trucking-insurance-idaho/" class="related-card">
          <h3>Idaho Trucking Insurance</h3>
          <p>Complete guide to insurance requirements for Idaho-based carriers.</p>
        </a>
        <a href="/trucking-insurance-idaho/chain-laws/" class="related-card">
