          <h3>Weight Limits & Permits</h3>
          <p>105,500 lb state limit, commodity exemptions, and permit types.</p>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section class="cta">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Get Compliant, Get Covered</h2>
      <p>Running legal in Idaho means keeping four registrations current: IRP, IFTA, UCR, and HVUT. Miss any one of them and you're risking fines, impoundment, or worse - being stranded at a weigh station 1,000 miles from home.</p>
      <p>RMS Truck Insurance works with Idaho carriers who want an agent that understands compliance. We verify your filings before binding, so you're not just insured - you're legal to haul.</p>

      <div class="cta-actions">
        <a href="tel:208-800-0640" class="btn">Call 208-800-0640</a>
        <a href="/trucking-insurance-idaho/" class="btn-outline">Back to Idaho Insurance</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- FOOTER NOTE -->
  <section class="footer-note">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="last-updated"><em>Last updated: January 2026</em></p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- MOBILE STICKY -->
  <div class="mobile-cta">
    <a href="tel:208-800-0640" class="mobile-btn">Get Idaho Quote - 208-800-0640</a>
  </div>

